The Gepetto module is a Python library for interacting with the IDA (Interactive Disassembler) software. It allows you to automate tasks and extract information from IDA databases using Python scripts. 
 
To use the Gepetto module, you will need to install it using pip install gepetto-ida. Once you have installed the module, you can import it into your Python scripts using import gepetto. You will also need to have IDA installed on your system and have an IDA database open to use the module.
